# Exercise 003 - Using host networking to expose database ports

1) Pull and run the "mysql" container image with the name "network-host-test";

2) Check that the service will be reachable on localhost on the port exposed by
   the container;

3) Stop the "network-host-test" container;

4) Pull and run the "mysql" container image with the name "network-host-test",
   exposing the 1234 port on the host;

5) Check that the service will be reachable on localhost on the port exposed by
   the container;

6) Is it possible? What happens?
